[{"short_id":"usdqtq","created_at":"2025-08-06T03:14:27.000-05:00","title":"Why are Windows semiannual updates named H1 and H2?","url":"https://devblogs.microsoft.com/oldnewthing/20250805-00/?p=111435","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"abareplace","user_is_author":false,"tags":["windows"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/usdqtq","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/usdqtq/why_are_windows_semiannual_updates_named"},{"short_id":"dstkgd","created_at":"2025-08-06T02:00:13.000-05:00","title":"Rethinking devtools: Escaping the Cloud and SaaS trap","url":"","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"\u003cp\u003eJust thinking out loud.\nIf not for a gazillion other reasons, a recent outage from Postman should remind us again why proper design decisions matter in devtools.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAPI workflows shouldn’t live in the cloud. A LOT of devtools shouldn’t live in the cloud. Some tools can’t work without it, all good. But a whole lot of them are there just because of some poor design choices.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYet…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNo cloud? No outage.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNo cloud? No sync issues.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNo cloud? No data security gaps.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo why keep forcing it where it doesn’t belong?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd it’s not even just the cloud. Cloud is awesome for some stuff. SaaS-like designs are dragging devtools into the same trap.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs a matter of fact, devtools in general shouldn’t feel like SaaS platforms. Unless we’re going through app usage dashboards - tabs, and mouse actions are not built for devs.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDevtools should prioritize developer control, not just pay-per-seat subscriptions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eP.S. No need to send me Postman alternatives. I already work on building an awesome one, but chose not to promote it in this post.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Just thinking out loud.\r\nIf not for a gazillion other reasons, a recent outage from Postman should remind us again why proper design decisions matter in devtools.\r\n\r\nAPI workflows shouldn’t live in the cloud. A LOT of devtools shouldn’t live in the cloud. Some tools can’t work without it, all good. But a whole lot of them are there just because of some poor design choices.\r\n\r\nYet…\r\n\r\n- No cloud? No outage.\r\n\r\n- No cloud? No sync issues.\r\n\r\n- No cloud? No data security gaps.\r\n\r\nSo why keep forcing it where it doesn’t belong?\r\n\r\nAnd it’s not even just the cloud. Cloud is awesome for some stuff. SaaS-like designs are dragging devtools into the same trap.\r\n\r\nAs a matter of fact, devtools in general shouldn’t feel like SaaS platforms. Unless we’re going through app usage dashboards - tabs, and mouse actions are not built for devs.\r\n\r\nDevtools should prioritize developer control, not just pay-per-seat subscriptions.\r\n\r\nP.S. No need to send me Postman alternatives. I already work on building an awesome one, but chose not to promote it in this post.","submitter_user":"kiselitza","user_is_author":true,"tags":["api","scaling","web"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dstkgd","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dstkgd/rethinking_devtools_escaping_cloud_saas"},{"short_id":"plofv3","created_at":"2025-08-06T01:25:45.000-05:00","title":"What it'll take to eradicate unintended breakage from Rust","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bUN54ByMp3U","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"pervognsen","user_is_author":false,"tags":["rust","video"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/plofv3","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/plofv3/what_it_ll_take_eradicate_unintended"},{"short_id":"umsj7d","created_at":"2025-08-06T01:25:27.000-05